WEBVTT

00:05.875 --> 00:07.249
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:14.708 --> 00:16.375
(SCREAMING)

00:17.333 --> 00:20.041
From now on, we have to assume
that whatever Claude sees

00:20.124 --> 00:21.750
and hears,
it sees and hears.

00:23.416 --> 00:25.667
You asked me where my people
are buried around here.

00:25.750 --> 00:29.958
The old Bear Cave.
It's been sealed since 1947.

00:30.583 --> 00:31.541
(MEN SHOUTING)

00:32.375 --> 00:34.583
HOLLY GIBNEY:
He's in there. We found him.

00:35.083 --> 00:36.917
RALPH ANDERSON: We're gonna
be back in a couple of hours.

00:37.416 --> 00:40.249
It's not right. Not telling them
that that thing's out there.

00:40.708 --> 00:42.958
What if it doesn't cotton
to being contained?

00:43.041 --> 00:45.124
Then we kill it
before it can kill us.

00:45.333 --> 00:46.792
What if it can't be killed?

00:48.750 --> 00:50.708
CLAUDE BOLTON:
Do you know what you just did?

00:51.083 --> 00:51.999
I know what I just did.

00:52.083 --> 00:53.541
I gave you the heads up
of your life.

00:53.875 --> 00:55.500
CLAUDE:
He's in my head, Seale.

00:55.583 --> 00:56.833
So, you just told that thing

00:56.917 --> 00:58.750
that all of those people
are coming for it.

00:58.833 --> 00:59.833
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

01:00.833 --> 01:01.708
(GUNSHOT)

01:01.792 --> 01:04.583
(EAR-SPLITTING RINGING)

01:04.667 --> 01:05.917
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:30.583 --> 01:32.625
-(GUNSHOTS)
-(JACK GROANS)

01:35.500 --> 01:36.917
There you go!

01:36.999 --> 01:39.375
(SHOTS CONTINUE)

01:41.999 --> 01:43.375
(BULLETS RICOCHET)

01:43.458 --> 01:45.500
-(YELPS)
-(GUNSHOT)

01:45.583 --> 01:47.333
-Jesus Christ!
-YUNIS SABLO: Fuck!

01:47.416 --> 01:48.500
(DISTORTED SNARLING)

01:50.833 --> 01:52.041
(SCREECHES)

01:56.333 --> 01:57.875
-(JACK GROANS)
-We gotta get outta here.

01:57.958 --> 02:00.833
-SABLO: And go where?
-I don't know. Just to get
the fuck outta here.

02:04.124 --> 02:05.541
ANDY KATCAVAGE:
Who's the shooter?

02:10.375 --> 02:11.917
(GUNSHOT)

02:11.999 --> 02:14.833
(YELLS) Jack!
We can talk about this!

02:15.625 --> 02:16.917
Motherf--!

02:16.999 --> 02:18.875
ANDY: No, no, no.
Come on, come on!

02:18.958 --> 02:21.166
(GUNSHOTS CONTINUE)

02:24.875 --> 02:27.166
(JACK GROANS)

02:28.041 --> 02:30.291
-Ah! Goddammit!
-Take this! Take this!

02:30.375 --> 02:33.416
(GROANS) Motherfucker!

02:36.500 --> 02:38.500
(HUMMING)

02:40.875 --> 02:42.249
SABLO: Is that fucking Howie?

02:46.750 --> 02:48.333
Uh-oh!

02:48.416 --> 02:50.667
JACK HOSKINS:
Oh, yeah, get in there.

02:50.750 --> 02:52.875
-Jesus Christ!
-SABLO: Keep going! Keep going!

02:52.958 --> 02:54.291
-Is that Pelley?
-Go! Go! Just go!

02:54.375 --> 02:56.375
-RALPH ANDERSON: Go!
-Get the fuck out!

02:56.458 --> 02:57.917
-Move!
-Jesus Christ!

02:57.999 --> 03:00.041
-(GUNSHOTS)
-HOWARD SALOMAN: Oh, my god!

03:01.249 --> 03:03.249
(GUNSHOTS CONTINUE)

03:05.958 --> 03:08.124
Hey, Seale, what the hell
you doin', man?

03:08.958 --> 03:10.249
(JACK GROANS)

03:13.500 --> 03:15.249
Motherfucker!

03:15.333 --> 03:17.375
(SNAKE TAIL RATTLES)

03:17.458 --> 03:19.083
Oh, no! Get off!

03:23.291 --> 03:24.875
-Go! Go, go!
-ANDY: Go now! Go now!

03:24.958 --> 03:27.208
CLAUDE BOLTON: Seale!
Seale, whatcha doin', man?

03:27.291 --> 03:28.458
RALPH: Get back here!

03:31.166 --> 03:32.541
(YELLS)

03:32.625 --> 03:34.208
CLAUDE:
Hey Seale, get back here!

03:34.291 --> 03:35.291
JACK: I got you.

03:35.792 --> 03:36.792
(GRUNTS)

03:38.750 --> 03:39.792
(INAUDIBLE)

03:42.166 --> 03:45.792
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

03:46.291 --> 03:47.291
Yeah!

03:59.208 --> 04:00.917
-Shit!
-(DRUNKENLY SINGING)

04:00.999 --> 04:03.375
Fucker! (PANTING)

04:03.458 --> 04:04.583
(GUNSHOT)

04:05.541 --> 04:08.708
-(GUNSHOT)
-I see you!

04:08.792 --> 04:11.416
-(SABLO YELLS, GROANS)
-RALPH: Oh shit!

04:11.500 --> 04:14.583
Fucker! Get up! Get up!
Up, up--

04:14.667 --> 04:17.500
Get up, up, up, up.
We don't have-- Go! Go!

04:17.583 --> 04:18.833
Oh, shit.

04:21.708 --> 04:23.083
HOWARD: Fuck!

04:23.166 --> 04:24.667
Let's get the fuck outta here!

04:27.583 --> 04:30.333
-(GRUNTS)
-Oh shit! Seale!

04:30.416 --> 04:33.041
RALPH: Claude! Don't go out!
Damn it! Don't!

04:34.041 --> 04:35.166
CLAUDE: Seale!

04:36.416 --> 04:37.958
Fuck!

04:38.041 --> 04:40.958
(DRUNKENLY GROANS)
Motherfucker!

04:41.041 --> 04:42.541
CLAUDE: Oh, God, man.

04:44.500 --> 04:47.792
They got him good, man.
Oh shit!

04:47.875 --> 04:50.708
Fuck! Oh! Oh shit!

04:50.792 --> 04:51.999
Oh, man.

04:53.083 --> 04:56.249
Fucking hurts to be shot, man.
Fucking hurts.

04:56.333 --> 04:59.124
RALPH:
Yeah. With the slugs he's using,

04:59.208 --> 05:01.124
you're lucky you didn't get
your arm taken off.

05:01.208 --> 05:03.208
-SABLO: Hurts to get shot.
-RALPH: You know what...

05:03.291 --> 05:05.541
ANDY: If we could just get
some fucking bars!

05:06.541 --> 05:08.041
Don't even think about it.

05:09.208 --> 05:11.208
Hey, when the GIs
were getting chewed up

05:11.291 --> 05:13.249
on the beaches on D-Day,
you know what they're told?

05:13.333 --> 05:16.124
Um... Uh-- Ad-- Advance or die.

05:16.208 --> 05:17.875
-Or something like that.
-That's fucking right.

05:17.958 --> 05:19.500
(GUNSHOT)

05:19.583 --> 05:20.625
RALPH: Can you fire lefty?

05:20.708 --> 05:22.124
SABLO:
Yeah, that's about all I can do.

05:22.208 --> 05:23.917
-Take this! Take this!
-No! No! No, no, no!

05:24.667 --> 05:25.708
HOLLY GIBNEY: Andy!

05:26.833 --> 05:28.249
What the hell is he doing?

05:28.333 --> 05:30.708
RALPH:
I don't fucking kn-- I think
he's going to get reception.

05:32.541 --> 05:35.958
Ah, Jesus, man. Why couldn't you
stay where you are?

05:36.583 --> 05:37.625
Son of a...

05:41.416 --> 05:42.999
-(GUNSHOT)
-Jesus!

05:43.083 --> 05:44.625
-(GUNSHOT)
-Fuck!

05:47.750 --> 05:49.833
-HOWARD: Go, Andy! Go!
-(ENGINE STARTS)

05:49.917 --> 05:55.500
-One... two... boom!
-(ANDY GRUNTS) Fuck!

05:55.583 --> 05:56.625
SABLO: Just go!

05:56.958 --> 05:57.958
Shit!

06:00.333 --> 06:01.375
RALPH: Go!

06:03.416 --> 06:05.083
Go! Go, Andy!

06:08.541 --> 06:09.583
HOWARD: Go, go, go!

06:11.917 --> 06:13.375
(PANTING)

06:28.875 --> 06:30.124
(GUNSHOT)

06:30.958 --> 06:32.083
-(GUNSHOT)
-(GRUNTS)

06:49.500 --> 06:50.583
What happened?

07:02.999 --> 07:04.667
Andy! No!

07:04.999 --> 07:06.166
No, no!

07:07.875 --> 07:11.041
HOWARD: No! No, no, no!
Holly, no! No, go back!

07:11.124 --> 07:13.124
-I'll get him. I'll get him. Go!
-No!

07:13.792 --> 07:14.833
Go back!

07:46.999 --> 07:48.875
(SCREAMING) Yeah!

07:48.958 --> 07:53.041
Mother nature!
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

07:53.917 --> 07:54.917
Ah!

08:11.333 --> 08:12.541
RALPH: (ECHOING SHOUT) Holly!

08:14.708 --> 08:15.708
Holly!

08:25.833 --> 08:29.291
Holly! Holly, get back here!

08:31.875 --> 08:32.875
Fuck!

08:32.958 --> 08:34.416
What the fuck is she doing?

08:34.500 --> 08:36.249
RALPH: Holly, get back here!

08:37.541 --> 08:38.583
Holly!

08:39.083 --> 08:40.583
Get back here!

08:54.708 --> 08:56.792
(YELLING, ECHOING)
Damn you to hell!

09:10.583 --> 09:12.416
(PANTING)

09:13.458 --> 09:15.541
Oh, he definitely will.

09:15.625 --> 09:17.750
-(SNARLS)
-(WINCES) Ow!

09:19.375 --> 09:20.416
Fuck!

09:22.708 --> 09:24.875
-Fuck you!
-(SNARLS)

09:24.958 --> 09:26.124
(JACK CRIES)

09:26.750 --> 09:29.416
-No more.
-(ROARS)

09:30.792 --> 09:32.208
(SNARLING, GROWLING)

09:32.291 --> 09:35.416
(SNAKE'S TAIL RATTLES)

09:35.958 --> 09:37.958
(PANTING)

09:43.625 --> 09:46.291
(CHUCKLES)
Come at me, motherfucker.

09:46.375 --> 09:47.416
-(SNAKE SNAPS)
-(SCREAMS)

09:47.500 --> 09:49.333
-(ROARS)
-(JACK'S SCREAMS ECHO)

09:52.166 --> 09:54.375
(JACK GROANS)

09:59.500 --> 10:00.708
RALPH: Holly!

10:01.625 --> 10:03.541
-(GUNSHOT)
-Fuck.

10:10.833 --> 10:12.375
Come on, come on.

10:13.917 --> 10:15.875
-Jack's done.
-(GUNSHOT)

10:15.958 --> 10:17.249
Tell Sablo
to save his ammunition,

10:17.333 --> 10:19.375
and tell him to stop shooting.
It's...

10:19.458 --> 10:20.999
It's splitting my head in two.

10:22.166 --> 10:23.333
It's time.

10:54.041 --> 10:55.041
(ROARS)

10:57.166 --> 10:58.208
(SNARLS)

11:06.541 --> 11:08.416
(GROWLS SOFTLY)

11:10.041 --> 11:13.750
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

11:43.458 --> 11:45.416
You're gonna be all right
out here by yourself?

11:45.500 --> 11:46.917
I'll be fine. You be careful.

11:49.124 --> 11:51.958
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

12:01.541 --> 12:05.124
(WHEEZING, GASPING)

12:14.833 --> 12:16.041
Ralph!

12:16.124 --> 12:19.083
(WHEEZING CONTINUES)

12:22.041 --> 12:23.416
SABLO: Put it down, Jack.

12:26.667 --> 12:28.792
Jack, just put it down, man.

12:28.875 --> 12:31.166
(JACK CONTINUES WHEEZING)

12:34.500 --> 12:35.708
JACK: It's in there.

12:38.416 --> 12:39.458
Kill it.

12:44.333 --> 12:45.375
No!

13:56.999 --> 13:58.124
(GATE CREAKS)

14:03.999 --> 14:05.917
-RALPH: Watch out.
-(HOLLY GASPS)

14:19.958 --> 14:21.750
-(WOOD CRACKS)
-(RALPH GRUNTS)

14:23.667 --> 14:25.041
HOLLY: You okay?

14:25.124 --> 14:27.875
Yeah... Yeah, yes.

14:29.583 --> 14:31.041
Uh, better be careful.

14:39.124 --> 14:41.416
(RALPH BREATHES DEEPLY)

14:50.750 --> 14:51.917
HOLLY: Look.

14:52.917 --> 14:55.041
He can be killed.

14:55.124 --> 14:58.083
-RALPH: How's that?
-HOLLY: He's scared of falling.

14:59.249 --> 15:00.458
Like us.

15:01.166 --> 15:02.500
(LEVER SQUEAKS)

15:15.124 --> 15:16.500
HOLLY: He's feeding.

15:18.458 --> 15:20.124
RALPH: Breadcrumbs from hell.

15:39.708 --> 15:40.958
(RALPH GRUNTS)

16:00.792 --> 16:02.041
(WATER SPLASHES)

16:27.999 --> 16:30.041
(ROCKS SHATTER, FALL)

16:41.541 --> 16:42.708
HOLLY: Stop.

16:57.625 --> 16:58.750
(HOLLY GRUNTS)

17:04.999 --> 17:06.416
HOLLY: He was in a frenzy.

17:12.416 --> 17:14.208
-RALPH: Holly.
-Hmm?

17:16.792 --> 17:17.917
RALPH: Look.

17:20.625 --> 17:22.124
This is where it happened.

17:28.875 --> 17:30.667
HOLLY: They're all in there.

17:30.750 --> 17:32.792
Must have been going crazy
trying to get to them.

17:32.875 --> 17:35.291
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

17:41.750 --> 17:43.124
-(WHISPERS) Holly.
-Hmm?

17:49.833 --> 17:50.917
RALPH: See it?

17:52.625 --> 17:53.667
The light?

18:45.667 --> 18:47.958
EL CUCO: (AS CLAUDE BOLTON)
Watch your step coming in.

18:48.041 --> 18:49.375
It's very slippery.

18:50.708 --> 18:54.083
Stay close to the walls in case
you need to grab onto something.

18:56.583 --> 18:59.541
You haven't come all this way
just to turn back now, have you?

19:24.041 --> 19:25.541
Well, howdy there, sheriff.

19:27.083 --> 19:29.541
And you must be the lovely
Miss Holly.

19:32.041 --> 19:33.999
Claude doesn't know
your last name,

19:34.083 --> 19:36.708
but he thinks about you
all the time.

19:39.083 --> 19:40.124
It's Gibney.

19:44.917 --> 19:46.083
Holly Gibney.

19:48.291 --> 19:49.583
EL CUCO: It's you
I have to thank

19:49.667 --> 19:52.541
for this situation
I find myself in, ain't it?

19:55.917 --> 19:58.291
I wanna know what made it
so easy for you

19:58.375 --> 19:59.750
to believe in me,

19:59.833 --> 20:02.041
and how on earth did she manage

20:02.124 --> 20:05.041
to convince a cowpoke
like you, sheriff.

20:08.583 --> 20:09.750
What are you?

20:10.875 --> 20:12.083
(EL CUCO SCOFFS)

20:13.875 --> 20:17.249
-What is your name?
-EL CUCO: Oh... you know.

20:18.124 --> 20:19.875
Where did you come from?

20:19.958 --> 20:22.041
-I don't remember.
-What is your nature?

20:22.124 --> 20:25.083
We're not very good answering
each other's questions, are we?

20:25.166 --> 20:27.375
-Are there more of you?
-Why?

20:27.458 --> 20:29.458
Have you seen
someone like me before?

20:30.416 --> 20:31.500
Are there others?

20:33.625 --> 20:36.166
'Cause there have been times
when I...

20:36.249 --> 20:38.583
-sense there could be more--
-Shut up.

20:43.041 --> 20:45.333
You really gon' pull
that trigger, sheriff?

20:48.458 --> 20:51.333
(BED CREAKS)

20:58.083 --> 20:59.708
Well, you go ahead and do it...

21:00.999 --> 21:02.500
if you don't mind dying.

21:05.875 --> 21:09.500
(YELLING) Will the real
Claude Bolton please stand up?

21:09.583 --> 21:12.833
-(ECHOING)
-(CAVE TREMORS, CRACKLES)

21:12.917 --> 21:14.833
(ROCKS SHATTERING, FALLING)

21:28.958 --> 21:31.583
-EL CUCO: You see?
-(RALPH GASPS) Step back!

21:31.667 --> 21:33.750
-(ECHOING)
-Stop yelling.

21:34.458 --> 21:36.208
(DEBRIS SCATTERING)

21:36.291 --> 21:40.166
EL CUCO: They're here, you know.
The dead.

21:40.249 --> 21:44.291
The rescuers that couldn't even
rescue themselves.

21:44.375 --> 21:46.875
But... you couldn't get to them,
could you?

21:48.416 --> 21:53.041
Well, it don't matter.
I still feel their presence.

21:53.124 --> 21:57.208
Especially the four Boltons.
They give off such a glow.

21:59.124 --> 22:00.208
Glow?

22:02.041 --> 22:05.041
They're the blood
that I'm becoming.

22:06.249 --> 22:07.541
It feels like...

22:09.375 --> 22:10.917
like I'm being entered.

22:11.792 --> 22:14.166
And what enters me, fills me.

22:15.625 --> 22:19.999
You have no idea
what it feels like to have

22:20.083 --> 22:22.333
all of that emotion
inside of me.

22:22.416 --> 22:23.333
Why children?

22:23.416 --> 22:25.792
(WHISPERS)
Stop asking him questions!

22:27.166 --> 22:29.750
I eat to survive, just like you.

22:29.833 --> 22:32.458
-Shut up.
-Why children?

22:36.375 --> 22:37.875
'Cause they taste the sweetest.

22:37.958 --> 22:39.583
-Motherfucker!
-HOLLY: Stop!

22:41.625 --> 22:42.708
He's poison.

22:51.166 --> 22:52.708
EL CUCO: I can't let you leave.

22:54.124 --> 22:55.291
You know that, right?

22:58.583 --> 22:59.625
HOLLY: No.

23:02.083 --> 23:03.667
We're the ones
who can't let you leave.

23:03.750 --> 23:05.041
(SCOFFS)

23:05.124 --> 23:06.583
RALPH:
Jack left one of us out there.

23:06.667 --> 23:09.041
He knows we're in here
and he knows what you are.

23:09.124 --> 23:10.166
He'll send more.

23:11.208 --> 23:12.291
I see.

23:14.875 --> 23:15.999
But I need to eat.

23:17.792 --> 23:18.833
(GUN COCKS)

23:25.792 --> 23:26.833
Claude.

23:27.500 --> 23:28.750
Put the gun down.

23:30.750 --> 23:31.917
HOLLY: Don't shoot.

23:34.708 --> 23:38.291
Don't shoot. If you shoot,
the whole chamber will fall
on our heads.

23:39.333 --> 23:40.708
RALPH: Hey, Claude.

23:41.792 --> 23:44.166
Just take your finger
off the trigger, okay?

23:50.124 --> 23:51.208
HOLLY: Claude, just...

23:52.583 --> 23:53.792
Just look at us.

23:56.083 --> 23:57.166
Just look at us.

23:58.416 --> 23:59.458
That's it.

24:00.958 --> 24:02.667
Now-- Now put the gun down.

24:07.917 --> 24:09.166
(DEEPLY INHALES)

24:19.500 --> 24:22.625
(GUNSHOT ECHOES)

24:22.708 --> 24:25.416
(ROCKS CRACKLES)

24:28.083 --> 24:29.375
HOLLY: Oh, my God.

24:30.708 --> 24:31.875
It's collapsing.

24:34.208 --> 24:36.708
RALPH: Move! Now! Now! Holly!

24:36.792 --> 24:38.124
HOLLY: Claude!

24:38.208 --> 24:39.375
RALPH: Holly!

24:42.333 --> 24:44.500
Cover your head!
Tuck your head!

24:45.416 --> 24:46.875
(ROCKS CRASHING)

24:49.041 --> 24:51.500
(CAVE RUMBLING)

25:00.541 --> 25:03.750
(SPLASHING)

25:16.458 --> 25:17.583
CLAUDE: Hey.

25:19.667 --> 25:20.792
Over here.

25:24.750 --> 25:25.792
(RALPH SIGHS)

25:28.958 --> 25:31.291
(CLAUDE GROANS) Sh...

25:31.375 --> 25:34.833
-I can't move.
-RALPH: Hold on-- Oh, shit.

25:34.917 --> 25:37.375
Okay. Um...

25:39.249 --> 25:40.291
Ready?

25:40.375 --> 25:43.625
-Three, two, one. Yeah.
-(HOLLY GRUNTS) Okay.

25:44.875 --> 25:47.083
-You got it?
-(PANTING)

25:47.375 --> 25:48.875
Oh, man.

25:48.958 --> 25:50.667
-You okay?
-Yeah, I'll live.

25:51.291 --> 25:53.291
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

25:54.333 --> 25:56.458
-Told you not to shoot.
-(HOLLY CHUCKLES)

26:03.500 --> 26:07.166
Okay. We'll be back in a moment,
okay? Hold tight.

26:07.249 --> 26:08.416
All right.

26:09.625 --> 26:11.083
Ah, fuck.

26:30.667 --> 26:31.708
RALPH: Hmm.

26:34.124 --> 26:35.667
HOLLY:
Do you have some kind of knife?

26:43.124 --> 26:44.208
Good.

26:52.500 --> 26:55.833
-(HOLLY GRUNTS)
-Yeah, Holly. Leave it.
Leave it. Leave it.

26:55.917 --> 26:58.083
If we were ever to claim
that this thing

26:58.166 --> 27:00.833
killed Frankie Peterson,
they'll write us off as loons.

27:00.917 --> 27:02.541
Terry's name
will never be cleared.

27:05.208 --> 27:06.333
Who's Terry?

27:12.875 --> 27:14.208
(GROANS)

27:18.249 --> 27:19.375
Did I kill him?

27:20.917 --> 27:23.249
HOLLY: Yeah. Yeah.

27:23.333 --> 27:25.208
RALPH: Okay, buddy.

27:25.291 --> 27:27.124
-We do this on three, yeah?
-HOLLY: Mm-hmm.

27:27.208 --> 27:30.333
-Okay. Three, two, one.
-HOLLY: Two, one.

27:30.416 --> 27:31.500
(CLAUDE GROANS)

27:34.333 --> 27:36.375
-HOLLY: Ooh-ooh-ooh.
-CLAUDE: Ah, shit.

27:39.875 --> 27:41.792
-RALPH: Watch your head.
-HOLLY: All right.

27:41.875 --> 27:43.833
-Yep.
-(CLAUDE GROANS)

27:45.833 --> 27:46.875
Ah, man.

27:54.999 --> 27:58.708
♪ (SINISTER MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

28:10.917 --> 28:12.083
HOLLY: What's wrong?

28:14.667 --> 28:16.792
-Nothing, I'll catch up.
-HOLLY: Okay.

28:27.249 --> 28:28.291
(RALPH GRUNTS)

28:31.041 --> 28:32.083
(SIGHS)

28:32.958 --> 28:34.958
Now look at you playing possum.

28:36.958 --> 28:38.083
How I know?

28:40.249 --> 28:42.249
What's left of your heart.

28:42.333 --> 28:45.124
Whatever it's called,
it's still pumpin'.

28:46.124 --> 28:48.291
Otherwise,
you got nothin' comin' out.

28:50.166 --> 28:51.166
Sawdust.

28:54.625 --> 28:56.917
I didn't know whether or not
you could be killed.

28:56.999 --> 28:59.792
I thought you could be
like anyone else, but...

29:01.625 --> 29:03.124
I'm not so sure anymore.

29:05.041 --> 29:08.333
I know that, uh,
this knife's certainly...

29:08.416 --> 29:12.875
isn't doing the trick.
Here's how I see it.

29:12.958 --> 29:14.999
You're weak.
You're getting weaker.

29:15.583 --> 29:16.833
You can't run.

29:17.541 --> 29:18.833
You can't hide.

29:20.208 --> 29:21.500
You can't hunt,

29:21.583 --> 29:25.583
which means you can't feed
and fill yourself.

29:25.667 --> 29:28.708
There's nothing stopping me
from just walking outta here
right now,

29:28.792 --> 29:31.583
come back with a bus load
of tourists and just watch them

29:31.667 --> 29:33.750
fucking push each other
out of the way,

29:33.833 --> 29:35.708
desperate, trying to get
the best angle

29:35.792 --> 29:38.083
of what's left
of your fucking face.

29:38.166 --> 29:40.999
-(GRUNTS)
-(EL CUCO GROWLS)

29:50.541 --> 29:54.208
And then comes the ever curious
scientific community.

29:55.166 --> 29:57.333
They're gonna be real interested
in you.

29:58.375 --> 30:02.124
Poking, probing, injecting,
extracting.

30:02.208 --> 30:04.416
They'll cut little pieces
of you off,

30:04.500 --> 30:06.667
take it back to the lab,

30:06.750 --> 30:10.999
Just keep fucking carving you
and carving you and carving you

30:11.083 --> 30:13.708
-until...
-(EL CUCO GROWLS SOFTLY)

30:13.792 --> 30:16.708
Yeah, you wouldn't want that,
would ya?

30:17.208 --> 30:18.249
(RALPH GRUNTS)

30:19.208 --> 30:21.333
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

30:23.249 --> 30:28.833
And it would serve our purposes
much better...

30:30.583 --> 30:34.667
if no one ever knew
that you ever existed.

30:36.792 --> 30:37.875
So...

30:40.083 --> 30:41.249
you gotta go.

30:43.792 --> 30:45.083
(EL CUCO SNARLS)

30:48.375 --> 30:50.416
(SKIN AND BONES CRACKLE)

30:51.083 --> 30:53.041
(BLOOD SQUELCHES)

31:06.124 --> 31:08.249
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

31:18.625 --> 31:19.833
♪ (MUSIC STOPS) ♪

31:52.208 --> 31:56.083
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

33:28.833 --> 33:29.917
(SIGHS)

33:33.500 --> 33:34.625
He, uh...

33:36.708 --> 33:38.291
He came here to be with me.

33:41.625 --> 33:43.041
That was the only reason.

33:50.625 --> 33:53.083
Holly, the locals could appear
at any stage.

33:53.166 --> 33:55.458
We need to talk pretty fast.

33:56.750 --> 33:58.249
Get our story straight.

34:12.708 --> 34:14.500
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

35:11.375 --> 35:14.500
(SIRENS WAIL IN DISTANCE)

35:21.416 --> 35:25.458
(SIRENS GROW LOUDER)

35:36.750 --> 35:43.667
(PHONE RINGS)

35:49.208 --> 35:50.917
Lieutenant Sablo from GBI.

35:59.208 --> 36:02.667
-Hayes.
-SABLO: Hayes, it's Sablo.

36:02.750 --> 36:05.041
We're down here
in Cecil, Tennessee.

36:05.124 --> 36:07.416
There was a shootout
in the parking lot.

36:07.500 --> 36:10.166
The gift shop,
Alec Pelley's dead.

36:10.249 --> 36:13.792
Howie Saloman is dead.
Jack Hoskins is dead.

36:15.583 --> 36:16.583
They're dead?

36:18.083 --> 36:21.083
SABLO: The shooter was a cop.
One of your own.

36:23.333 --> 36:24.500
But he didn't act alone.

36:24.583 --> 36:27.458
In fact, he was compelled
to kill by someone else.

36:28.208 --> 36:30.083
Like... he had an accomplice?

36:30.166 --> 36:32.166
SABLO: No, I'm saying Hoskins
was the accomplice.

36:32.249 --> 36:34.958
The alpha who I believe killed
Frankie Peterson

36:35.041 --> 36:37.875
is still out there. He
attempted to grab another boy

36:37.958 --> 36:41.291
down here two nights ago.
He got away,

36:41.375 --> 36:44.958
but we got him on video,
so I'm gonna send you the link.

36:45.041 --> 36:46.375
Wait, wait, wait.
Hold on, just, uh...

36:46.458 --> 36:48.667
SABLO:
It's nobody's fault, okay?

36:48.750 --> 36:51.375
But I believe certain decisions
coming out of your office

36:51.458 --> 36:53.500
need to be revisited.
Wouldn't you agree?

36:56.958 --> 36:59.416
RALPH: So, Seale Bolton
receives a phone call

36:59.500 --> 37:02.583
from an unknown individual
who says he works with me.

37:02.667 --> 37:06.667
This individual claims to have
knowledge of the whereabouts

37:06.750 --> 37:10.333
of a more likely suspect
in the Frankie Peterson murder.

37:12.416 --> 37:13.875
SABLO: You wanna tell me
what happened, Claude?

37:13.958 --> 37:16.083
-CLAUDE: I already told you.
-Well, I'd like
to hear it again.

37:16.166 --> 37:19.625
(CLAUDE SIGHS)
Detective Sablo and Anderson,

37:19.708 --> 37:22.833
they came to interview me
when the Cherokee County DA

37:22.917 --> 37:26.041
was considering reopening
the Frank Peterson homicide.

37:26.124 --> 37:27.249
SABLO: Why you?

37:27.333 --> 37:29.541
Because I identified the man
they arrested for it,

37:29.625 --> 37:32.667
Terry Maitland, when he walked
into the Peach Crease,
covered in blood.

37:32.750 --> 37:34.083
But the more
you thought about it...

37:34.166 --> 37:35.416
CLAUDE: Well, the more
I thought about it,

37:35.500 --> 37:38.750
the more I-- I realized
I made a mistake. It wasn't him.

37:38.833 --> 37:41.291
It was just someone who looked
a little like him. That's all.

37:42.792 --> 37:44.792
HAYES: Witnesses
from the Peterson homicide.

37:44.875 --> 37:46.625
I need the transcripts
from the interviews.

37:57.667 --> 38:00.750
DETECTIVE:
This caller, did he specifically
tell you where to find him?

38:00.833 --> 38:03.833
Yeah, the abandoned
souvenir shop on the side

38:03.917 --> 38:05.708
of that hill,
so we went to investigate.

38:05.792 --> 38:07.917
-DETECTIVE: You went there?
-Yeah. My assumption is that

38:07.999 --> 38:09.833
he's there to take out
Claude Bolton,

38:09.917 --> 38:11.375
who he perceives as a threat.

38:11.458 --> 38:13.083
Him being Jack Hoskins.

38:13.166 --> 38:16.041
The detective from your squad
who's been in the wind

38:16.124 --> 38:18.458
for kidnapping,
attempted murder.

38:18.541 --> 38:19.708
The same.

38:21.166 --> 38:24.500
Yeah, so, I, uh...
interpreted the phone call

38:24.583 --> 38:26.833
as being made to set up
an ambush.

38:26.917 --> 38:28.249
Frankly, I thought
the whole thing

38:28.333 --> 38:29.917
was gonna turn out
to be bullshit.

38:31.458 --> 38:32.583
Was wrong.

38:38.041 --> 38:38.999
(PANTING)

38:39.083 --> 38:41.583
How long they gonna keep
my brother's body for?

38:41.667 --> 38:43.375
Hopefully not for too long.

38:43.458 --> 38:45.291
CLAUDE:
Well, how long is not too long?

38:45.375 --> 38:47.375
Claude,
tell me about the phone call.

38:53.541 --> 38:55.249
March 3rd through the 7th,

38:55.333 --> 38:58.249
Maitland's last visit
to see his father, um...

38:59.458 --> 39:04.083
On my investigation,
I encountered Mr. Katcavage,

39:04.166 --> 39:08.500
uh... former Dayton PD detective
who had worked dozens

39:08.583 --> 39:11.958
of homicides over the years.
I found him...

39:15.124 --> 39:17.667
I found him, uh,
highly competent,

39:17.750 --> 39:20.124
so I recommended
that my employer...

39:20.208 --> 39:22.166
hire him as part of the team.

39:22.249 --> 39:25.083
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

39:46.375 --> 39:49.166
♪ If you stop ♪

39:49.249 --> 39:54.458
♪ To catch your breath ♪

39:58.333 --> 39:59.792
Hey, darlin', it's me.

40:00.708 --> 40:02.333
So if we're gonna pull this off,
Jeannie,

40:02.416 --> 40:04.375
there's something I need you
to do.

40:04.458 --> 40:07.249
♪ ...At your heels ♪

40:12.124 --> 40:19.124
♪ You may find
That loneliness ♪

40:24.583 --> 40:27.917
♪ Is indeed ♪

40:27.999 --> 40:33.333
♪ Your oldest friend ♪

40:44.999 --> 40:47.166
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

40:48.041 --> 40:49.708
Thank you. Thank you.

41:04.041 --> 41:07.208
JEANNIE ANDERSON:
Whether you accept or reject
the reality of that thing,

41:07.291 --> 41:10.416
it's not important right now.
What is important...

41:11.583 --> 41:13.208
is that when they ask you,

41:13.958 --> 41:15.416
and they will definitely ask you

41:15.500 --> 41:17.708
about that meeting
with Holly Gibney,

41:18.917 --> 41:21.750
please don't mention anything
about shape shifters

41:21.833 --> 41:27.917
or El Cucos or anything
that might sound supernatural.

41:28.500 --> 41:29.541
Okay?

41:30.708 --> 41:31.750
Otherwise...

41:33.208 --> 41:34.375
I can do that.

41:35.375 --> 41:39.333
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

41:42.708 --> 41:47.583
♪ You may awake ♪

41:47.667 --> 41:51.541
♪ In the night ♪

41:54.792 --> 42:01.249
♪ And wonder who you are ♪

42:07.541 --> 42:14.625
♪ If you don't turn on
The light ♪

42:33.124 --> 42:40.124
♪ You may remain a lost star ♪

42:47.458 --> 42:51.500
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

43:01.291 --> 43:03.625
What I've come to tell you
today, Mrs. Maitland...

43:07.249 --> 43:09.041
is that there have been
certain developments

43:09.124 --> 43:12.166
in the Frankie Peterson
homicide case.

43:13.999 --> 43:17.999
Some new avenues of inquiry
have opened.

43:25.166 --> 43:26.541
We're reopening the case.

43:31.667 --> 43:33.667
What about your slam dunk
forensics?

43:35.750 --> 43:37.917
Well, we reexamined
the perp DNA

43:37.999 --> 43:40.416
we got from the crime scene
and discovered that

43:40.500 --> 43:43.583
what we actually had
was a mixture of samples,

43:43.667 --> 43:44.875
perp and the victim,

43:44.958 --> 43:46.124
which makes it unreliable
in court.

43:46.208 --> 43:49.249
Girls, I need you
to go upstairs, please.

43:59.625 --> 44:02.291
On Monday, I'm holding
a press conference

44:02.375 --> 44:04.875
to announce the reopening
of the investigation...

44:06.541 --> 44:12.041
and to officially go on record
regarding the dropping

44:12.124 --> 44:13.875
of charges
against Terry Maitland.

44:17.999 --> 44:19.541
Your family has suffered enough,

44:19.625 --> 44:22.208
and I just want to do
whatever I...

44:29.208 --> 44:33.792
Because of your pending lawsuits
against me and my office...

44:35.750 --> 44:38.083
I have to refrain
from telling you

44:38.708 --> 44:40.083
what is in my heart.

44:42.750 --> 44:44.083
I completely understand.

44:54.041 --> 44:55.083
(SIGHS)

45:00.999 --> 45:02.416
MAYA MAITLAND:
Was he mean to you?

45:05.625 --> 45:07.249
No, my love,
he wasn't mean to me.

45:38.541 --> 45:39.667
Flying or driving?

45:40.625 --> 45:41.625
HOLLY: Driving.

45:44.291 --> 45:46.541
About ten hours, right? Chicago?

45:46.625 --> 45:47.750
-Yeah.
-Ten hours?

45:47.833 --> 45:51.958
I have a couple of stops
I have to make along the way.

45:53.999 --> 45:56.166
RALPH: You know, I wouldn't mind
teaming up again,

45:56.249 --> 45:58.416
the opportunity ever arose.

45:58.500 --> 46:00.166
I mean,
preferably on something simple

46:00.249 --> 46:02.999
like a gangland triple homicide.
Something like that.

46:05.041 --> 46:06.999
When I was in the caves,

46:07.083 --> 46:10.375
El Cuco asked me,
uh, why I was so open

46:10.458 --> 46:12.375
to believing in its existence.

46:14.875 --> 46:17.875
My father was ex-military
and when I was little,

46:17.958 --> 46:20.999
he would say,
"A man knows a man."

46:22.999 --> 46:26.625
Well, if I had the time
to think in that cave

46:26.708 --> 46:29.375
and the inclination to answer
that thing,

46:29.458 --> 46:30.792
I would have said...

46:32.166 --> 46:34.667
"An outsider knows an outsider."

46:38.583 --> 46:40.041
(DEEPLY INHALES)

46:58.500 --> 47:01.541
Holly. What else is out there?

47:20.375 --> 47:21.416
(SIGHS)

48:19.750 --> 48:23.750
RALPH: I never told you but...
I saw Derek.

48:25.625 --> 48:27.958
He... spoke to me.

48:29.458 --> 48:31.375
-JEANNIE: What did he say?
-RALPH: Well, it--

48:31.458 --> 48:33.875
it wasn't Derek, so...

48:33.958 --> 48:36.625
Ralph-- Tell me what he said.
Just humor me.

48:39.083 --> 48:41.333
He said that I need
to let him go.

48:44.041 --> 48:45.124
Let him go?

48:47.708 --> 48:50.833
-Well, fat chance of that.
-(CHUCKLES)

49:00.166 --> 49:01.667
I don't know.

49:01.750 --> 49:04.333
I like to think the way
this whole experience...

49:06.833 --> 49:08.124
cracked the world open.

49:09.833 --> 49:11.541
Maybe the next time he appears,

49:12.458 --> 49:14.375
maybe it's gonna be
the real Derek.

49:16.166 --> 49:18.833
Or maybe after a few years pass,

49:19.667 --> 49:20.792
many more years,

49:21.541 --> 49:22.875
we'll just go visit him.

49:25.750 --> 49:27.875
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

51:01.708 --> 51:07.249
♪ (SINISTER MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

51:07.333 --> 51:08.583
(HOLLY GASPS)

51:14.500 --> 51:16.625
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

51:26.416 --> 51:30.041
♪ (DISTORTED MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

51:30.124 --> 51:31.833
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

